<li id="S0.I1.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">2.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">(Blackwell-Girshick) Further assume that <math id="S0.I1.i2.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="X_{n},N\in\mathcal{L}^{2}" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mi>N</mi></mrow><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">ℒ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></math>. Prove that</p>
<ol id="S0.I1.I1" class="ltx_enumerate">
<li id="S0.I1.i2.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">(a)</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p1" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p"><math id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathbb{E}[S_{N}^{2}]=\mathbb{E}[N]\text{Var}[X_{1}]+\mathbb{E}[N^{2}]\mathbb{%&#10;E}[X_{1}]^{2}" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msubsup><mi>S</mi><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi>N</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>Var</mtext><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msup><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>⁢</mo><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></p>
</div></li>
<li id="S0.I1.i2.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">(b)</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i2.p1" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p"><math id="S0.I1.i2.i2.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\text{Var}[S_{N}]=\mathbb{E}[N]\text{Var}[X_{1}]+\text{Var}[N]\mathbb{E}[X_{1}%&#10;]^{2}" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mtext>Var</mtext><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>N</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi>N</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>Var</mtext><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mtext>Var</mtext><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi>N</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>⁢</mo><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></p>
</div></li>
</ol>
</div>
<div id="Thmhintx2" class="ltx_theorem ltx_theorem_hint">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_title_theorem"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_theorem"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Hint</span></span>.</h6>
<div id="Thmhintx2.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Same trick as with Wald’s equation.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i2.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Similarly to Wald’s equation we have</p>
<table id="S0.EGx3" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex7"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex7.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\mathbb{E}[S_{N}^{2}]" display="inline"><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msubsup><mi>S</mi><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex7.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\mathbb{E}[\mathbbm{1}_{N=n}S_{n}^{2}]" display="inline"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle="true"><munderover><mo largeop="true" movablelimits="false" symmetric="true">∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∞</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><msub><mn>𝟙</mn><mrow><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>⁢</mo><msubsup><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
<tbody id="S0.Ex8"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex8.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\mathbb{E}[\mathbbm{1}_{N=n}]\mathbb{E}[S_{n}%&#10;^{2}]" display="inline"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle="true"><munderover><mo largeop="true" movablelimits="false" symmetric="true">∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∞</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mn>𝟙</mn><mrow><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>⁢</mo><mi>𝔼</mi><mo>⁢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msubsup><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></td>
